<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-788] contrib/benchmark assumes Locale.US for parsing dates in Reuters collection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-788</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;SimpleDateFormat used for parsing dates in Reuters documents is instantiated without specifying a locale. So it is using the default locale. If that happens to be US, it will work. But for another locale a parse exception is likely.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Affects both StandardBenchmarker and ReutersDocMaker.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix is trivial - specify Locale.US for SimpleDateFormat&apos;s constructor.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
